{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KJUokdHPdJ7UF21qPNkvwk","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me compile the final report with all the URL routing information I've found:\n\n## Summary of URL Routing in Cloche\n\nI've completed a thorough search of the codebase. Here's the comprehensive breakdown of all URL routing patterns:\n\n### HTTP Route Registration (Main Routing File)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 139-158)\n\nThe routes are registered in the `NewHandler()` function using Go's `http.ServeMux` with the Go 1.22+ pattern routing syntax:\n\n#### HTML Pages (User-facing routes):\n- `GET /{$}` → `handleProjectOverview` - Landing page showing all projects\n- `GET /runs` → `handleRunsList` - Lists all runs (with optional `?project=` filter)\n- `GET /runs/{id}` → `handleRunDetail` - Details page for a specific run\n- `GET /projects/{name}` → `handleProjectDetail` - Project detail page\n\n#### API Routes:\n- `GET /api/projects` → `handleAPIProjects` - List all projects as JSON\n- `GET /api/runs` → `handleAPIRuns` - List runs as JSON (supports `?project=` query parameter)\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}` → `handleAPIRunDetail` - Get run details as JSON\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` → `handleAPIStepOutput` - Fetch step output logs\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` → `handleAPIStream` - Server-Sent Events stream for live logs\n- `DELETE /api/runs/{id}/container` → `handleAPIDeleteContainer` - Delete a retained container\n- `POST /api/projects/{name}/trigger` → `handleAPITriggerOrchestrator` - Trigger orchestrator\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator` → `handleAPIOrchestratorStatus` - Get orchestrator status\n- `POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/start` → `handleAPIOrchestratorStart`\n- `POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/stop` → `handleAPIOrchestratorStop`\n- `POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/concurrency` → `handleAPIOrchestratorConcurrency`\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/info` → `handleAPIProjectInfo` - Project metadata\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff` → `handleAPIPromptDiff` - Git diff for prompts\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows` → `handleAPIWorkflows` - List workflows\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` → `handleAPIStepContent`\n- `GET /static/` → File server (static assets from embedded FS)\n\n### Key URL Patterns\n\n#### Project Filtering on Runs Page\n- **Template Reference:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` (line 55)\n- **Pattern:** `/runs?project={projectDir}`\n- **Example usage in JavaScript:** `window.location.href = '/runs?project=' + encodeURIComponent(dir);`\n- **Handler code:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 248-249)\n  - Extracts filter: `projectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")`\n  - Conditional filtering: If projectFilter != \"\", uses `ListRunsByProject()`, else uses `ListRuns()`\n\n#### Direct Links to Runs by Project\n- **Template Reference:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` (line 27)\n- **Pattern:** `<a href=\"/runs?project={{.Dir}}\" class=\"btn btn-secondary\">View Runs</a>`\n- **Template Reference:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (line 8)\n- **Pattern:** `<a href=\"/runs?project={{.Dir}}\" class=\"btn btn-secondary btn-sm\">View all runs</a>`\n\n### Template Files with URL Generation\n\nAll templates are in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/`:\n\n1. **layout.html** - Base template with navigation\n2. **projects.html** - Project overview cards (lines 9, 27)\n3. **runs.html** - Runs list (lines 31, 55, 57, 63, 84)\n4. **run_detail.html** - Run detail page (lines 3, 103, 128, 194, 225)\n5. **project_detail.html** - Project detail page (lines 6, 8, 44, 56, 75, 82, 90, 131, 143, 274)\n\n### Static Assets\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n\nServed via: `GET /static/` route (stripped prefix handler)\n\n### Frontend URL Navigation\n\nThe frontend JavaScript generates URLs using the patterns:\n- Direct HTML: `href=\"/runs?project={{.Dir}}\"`\n- JavaScript: `window.location.href = '/runs?project=' + encodeURIComponent(dir);`\n- Fetch API: `/api/runs?project=` + encoded project directory\n\n### Server Initialization\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` (lines 102-126)\n\n- HTTP server is optional (enabled via `CLOCHE_HTTP` env var or config)\n- Web handler is created with options for container logging, log store, log broadcaster\n- Listens on configurable address (default would be set in config)\n\nAll routes use Go 1.22+ style pattern matching with `http.ServeMux.HandleFunc()`, providing clean separation of HTTP methods and path patterns."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a2abdaeecdfbece0c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 61279\ntool_uses: 17\nduration_ms: 29227</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc9fd8a8-bf87-49d2-bf62-1ae5b9ba4dc0","uuid":"8bf2cc4e-fecc-4a1f-aa8e-e4ad41d66ac1","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to find all code related to URL routing, especially:\n1. Where routes are defined (HTTP handlers, mux setup, router configuration)\n2. Any references to \"runs?project=\" or runs URL patterns\n3. Any references to \"projects/\" URL patterns\n4. Templates or frontend code that generates URLs to the runs page\n\nSearch thoroughly across the codebase for:\n- Route registration patterns (http.HandleFunc, mux.Handle, router patterns)\n- URL patterns containing \"runs\" or \"projects\"\n- Query parameter usage for \"project\" in the context of runs\n- Any HTML templates or frontend code with links to runs\n\nLook in directories like: cmd/, internal/, internal/adapters/, templates/, web/, static/, etc.","agentId":"a2abdaeecdfbece0c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me compile the final report with all the URL routing informati